# Parameterized FIFO Design & Verification (SystemVerilog with Coverage)

Overview

This project implements and verifies a parameterized synchronous FIFO (First-In-First-Out) using SystemVerilog. The verification includes assertion-based checks and functional coverage to ensure correctness across normal and corner-case scenarios.

 Objective

* Design a configurable FIFO with parameterized depth and width
* Verify correct data flow and flag behavior
* Detect overflow and underflow conditions
* Achieve functional coverage using SystemVerilog covergroups

---
Features

* Parameterized FIFO (configurable depth and width)
* Full and empty flag generation
* Pointer and counter-based architecture
* Assertion-based verification
* Functional coverage using covergroups

---
Design Description

The FIFO design uses:

* Write pointer (`wr_ptr`) to store incoming data
* Read pointer (`rd_ptr`) to retrieve data
* Counter (`count`) to track the number of elements

Conditions:

* Full → `count == DEPTH`
* Empty → `count == 0`

---
 Verification Methodology

* Developed a SystemVerilog testbench
* Generated stimulus using `$urandom`
* Performed write and read operations
* Verified FIFO behavior using waveform analysis in QuestaSim

---

## Assertions

Assertion checks were implemented to detect invalid operations:

* Overflow: Write when FIFO is full
* Underflow: Read when FIFO is empty

Errors are reported during simulation using `$error`.

---
Functional Coverage

Functional coverage was implemented using SystemVerilog covergroups.

Coverpoints:

* Write enable (`wr_en`)
* Read enable (`rd_en`)
* Full flag (`full`)
* Empty flag (`empty`)

Cross Coverage:

* Write when FIFO is full (overflow condition)
* Read when FIFO is empty (underflow condition)

Coverage Goal:

* Ensure all operational and corner-case scenarios are exercised

Result:

* Achieved 100% functional coverage

---
Simulation Results

* FIFO maintains correct First-In-First-Out behavior
* Data is read in the same order as written
* Assertions detect invalid conditions
* Coverage confirms all scenarios are exercised

